rComments: Matei was a good prof. Even though, lectures become too theoretical, his handwriting is hard to read from time to time, this course is in general quite hard, the exams were straightforward, he responds to emails fast and the labs were interesting. Assignments, problems solved during classes and tutorials are the best ways to practise for the exams.

Professor is great, the content is what makes this course difficult. Homework problems are tough but are good practice, labs were somewhat difficult online so try to do them in person if possible. Midterm was fair, this class is tough but a good grade is reachable if you give it the time it requires.

Fluids is a difficult class but Matei is an honest professor that wants you to pass if you will do the work. He doesnt like holding students back like other professors who dont care. I would recommend him to any student who is taking the class for the first time or retaking the course again.

Matei's actually a good prof. Cares for his students. He actually wants you to pass. I ended up understanding the course into depth and I generally liked the course. His handwriting isn't the best so his notes were hard to read. Once I understood it though, paired with his typed out notes I was good to go

Very nice professor and always reachable outside of class. Personally didn't learn much during the lectures as questions often got sidetracked to other discussion topics. Exams are fair and what is taught in the dgds is good for the tests.

Good Professor, He really wants you to learn the material.  You don't need to buy the book for gas dynamics to do well. But, buy the book if you love the material and for your research reference.  He has notes he gives you to study.  The course is also very interesting.  I would say its a must take course for fluid dynamics enthusiasts.
Great prof! Makes engineering really interesting. Relatively easy courses
He is a great prof. Really funny and knows his stuff. Very reasonable with marking and accomodating.
